The '''Balkan Peace Park'''<ref name="Gazeta Standard">{{cite news|url=http://lajme.shqiperia.com/lajme/artikull/iden/1046907951/titulli/Parku-Ballkanik-i-Paqes|title=The Balkanic Park of Peace|last=Gazeta Standard|date=6 August 2010|language=Albanian|accessdate=6 August 2010}}</ref> is a proposed park<ref name=registar>Study on the rationality of proclaiming the Prokletije region as National Park [http://www.ks-gov.net/akmm/dokumente/Studim%20mbi%20arsyeshmerine%20e%20shpalljes%20se%20territorit%20te%20Bjeshkeve%20te%20Nemuna%20Park%20Nacional.pdf ''Republic of Kosovo''] {{sq icon}}</ref> ({{lang-sq|Parku Ballkanik i Paqes}}, [[Serbian language|Serbian]] and {{lang-cg|''Balkanski mirovni park''}}<ref>{{cite news |title=Na Maju jezerce <U+010D>etvrti put |first= |last= |newspaper=[[Vijesti]] |date=18 March 2010 |location=Podgorica |url=http://www.b92.net/putovanja/vesti.php?nav_id=418660 |language=Montenegrin}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Prokletije - Balkanski park mira |first=T. |last=<U+0160>o<U+0161>ki<U+0107> |newspaper=[[Pobjeda]] |date=14 June 2007 |location=Podgorica |url=http://www.pobjeda.co.me/citanje.php?datum=2007-06-14&id=120106 |language=Montenegrin}}</ref>) located in the western part of [[Kosovo]], north-eastern part of [[Albania]] and south-eastern part of [[Montenegro]].<ref name=registar>Institute for Nature Conservation of Serbia: [http://www.natureprotection.org.rs/images/stories/pdf/registar_zasticenih_dobara_latinica.pdf ''Registry of Protected Natural Resources''] {{sr icon}}</ref><ref name=ministry>{{cite book
  |authorlink = David Mumford
  |title = Protected Natural Resources in Serbia
  |publisher = Ministry of Environmental Protection, Institute for Nature Conservation of Serbia
  |year = 2007
  |isbn = 978-86-80877-82-0 {{Please check ISBN|reason=Check digit (0) does not correspond to calculated figure.}}}}</ref><ref name="Sulejmani">{{cite news|title=Bashkepunimi rajonal bisedime per nje park kombetar shqiptaro-kosovaro-malazez |url=http://www.alsat.tv/lajme-nga-vendi/bashkepunimi-rajonal-bisedime-per-nje-park-kombetar-shqiptaro-kosovaro-malazez.html|year=2009|last=Sulejmani|first=Edlira|work=Alsattv|language=Albanian|accessdate=28 July 2010}}</ref> The terrain is rugged and the park is home to the highest mountains in the [[Dinaric Alps]]. [[Maja Jezerce]] {{convert|2694|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} in Albania and [[<U+0110>eravica]] in Kosovo is {{convert|2656|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} high. Many lakes are found there especially on the Albanian side.

Also this park contains many rare species of animals like the brown bear. The main towns and villages are [[Pe<U+0107><U+200E>]], [[De<U+010D>ani]] and [[Junik]] in Kosovo and [[Tropoj<U+00EB>]] and [[Bajram Curri (town)|Bajram Curri]] in Albania. This parks is also home to the [[Prokletije]] or Albanian Alps where old Albanian traditions are still used.

